## Idea

Given a Lie algebra $\mathfrak{g}$ over the [[real numbers]] or [[complex numbers]], and gives a choice $\{t_0, t_a\}_{a \in I}$ of [[linear basis]] of $\mathfrak{g}$, the corresponding _InÃ¶nÃ¼-Wigner contraction_ is the Lie algebra obtained by "sending $t_0$ to zero", i.e. the Lie algebra obtained from the previous one by passing to basis elements $\{\epsilon t_0, t_a\}_{a \in I}$ with $\epsilon$ in the ground field, in the [[limit of a sequence|limit]] that $\epsilon \to 0$.


